  "id": "WebSpark.HttpClientUtility",
  "version": "2.6.0",
  "description": "Drop-in HttpClient wrapper for .NET 8-10 with Polly resilience, response caching, OpenTelemetry, and batch execution orchestration. One-line setup eliminates boilerplate for retries, circuit breakers, correlation IDs, and structured logging. Perfect for microservices, APIs, and web scrapers. Includes authentication providers (Bearer, Basic, API Key), concurrent requests, fire-and-forget operations, streaming support, and environment x user x request batch runs with progress and statistics. Supports .NET 8 LTS (until Nov 2026), .NET 9, and .NET 10. For web crawling features, see WebSpark.HttpClientUtility.Crawler package.",
